Five of family killed as truck overturns, hits hut 
5-3-2017 
Five members of a family, including three minors, were killed when a dumper truck overturned and hit their hut in Jalaun district, police said on Sunday. According to a spokesperson of Uttar Pradesh Police, the incident took place at around 11.45 pm last night when a dumper truck turned upside down and hit a roadside hut, killing five persons on the spot.

WATCH WHAT ELSE IS IN THE NEWS

The deceased have been identified as Pappu (45), Maya (40), Nandini (14), Dheeru (10) and Jai (8) — all members of the same family — police said, adding that efforts were on to nab the driver who is absconding. 
